SIMPLE: entire
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Entire
<hw>En*tire"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>entier</ets>, L. <ets>integer</ets> untouched, undiminished,
entire; pref. <ets>in-</ets>, negative + the root of <ets>tangere</ets>
to touch. See <er>Tangent</er>, and cf. <er>Integer</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Complete in all parts; undivided; undiminished; whole;
full and perfect; not deficient; <as>as, the <ex>entire</ex> control of
a business; <ex>entire</ex> confidence, ignorance.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That ye may be perfect and <qex>entire</qex>, wanting nothing.</q>
<rj><qau>James i. 4.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With strength <qex>entire</qex> and free will armed.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>One <qex>entire</qex> and perfect chrysolite.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Without mixture or alloy of anything; unqualified;
morally whole; pure; faithful.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Pure fear and <qex>entire</qex> cowardice.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>No man had ever a heart more <qex>entire</qex> to the king.</q>
<rj><qau>Clarendon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Consisting of a
single piece, as a corolla.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Having an evenly
continuous edge, as a leaf which has no kind of teeth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Not gelded; -- said of a horse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Internal; interior.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- See <er>Whole</er>, and
<er>Radical</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Entire</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Entire
<hw>En*tire"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Entirely.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧Too long to print in <xex>entire</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Thackeray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Brewing)</fld> <def>A name originally given to a
kind of beer combining qualities of different kinds of beer.</def>
<mark>[Eng.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Foker's <xex>Entire</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Thackeray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Entirely</ent>⟦br⟧
